The above in response to someone ( seemingly in a tank-class group ) complaining about not getting a Symbol buff during the raid.<br>
<br>
For those of us who weren't there, and didn't hear the explanation, what is the determining factor for who gets a symbol buff in a KCoG-typical dragon raid? Is it reserved for only &quot;tank&quot; classes ( War, SK, Pal ), or Melee ( tank + bard, rogue, monk ), or is there some other method of determining who gets this important buff for damage-takers?<br>
<br>
Our Guild will be joining the KCoG soon, and the more I learn about your processes, then better. <p>-Zymyool, Officer and WebMaster for the <a href="http://members.cox.net/ancient" target="_blank">Ancient Adventurers</b></a> on the Karana Server
